<subSubSection lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,1890,2023]" lastBlockId="44.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1962,1987]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Description.</emphasis>
Colony encrusting, uni- to multilaminar. Zooids hexagonal, becoming polygonal with increasing calcification, generally longer than wide, delimited by slightly raised sinuous margins. Frontal shield heavily calcified, uniformly punctured by 36–51 pseudopores, granular. Primary orifice somewhat hoof-shaped, longer than wide, with arcuate anter delimited from broader concave poster by 2 downcurved condyles at about one-third zooid length. Secondary orifice surrounded by 4 solid tubercles. Frontal avicularia small, elliptical, usually 1, rarely 2, per zooid, placed at proximal zooidal margin. Interzooidal avicularia absent. Ooecium subglobose, as long as wide; ectooecium granular with median slit-like membranous area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="45" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</emphasis>
When 
<bibRefCitation author="Canu, F. &amp; Bassler, R. S." box="[398,674,332,357]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref30220" refString="Canu, F. &amp; Bassler, R. S. (1930 a) The Bryozoan Fauna of the Galapagos Islands. Proceedings of United States National Museum, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, 76 (2810), 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="1930">Canu &amp; Bassler (1930a)</bibRefCitation>
described this species they stated that the specimen lacked ooecia. Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[371,469,367,392]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">holotype</typeStatus>
by SEM, however, showed that two zooids have ooecia, each with a proximally facing slit-like ectooecial frontal membranous window (not visible in 
<figureCitation box="[863,1001,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1939,1961]" captionTargetBox="[187,1409,507,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-203@44.[181,1415,503,1912]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 27. Trematooecia hexagonalis (Canu &amp; Bassler, 1930). A–F, USNM 8513, holotype, Galápagos Islands. A, B, groups of zooids. C, close-up of zooids and opercula. D, primary orifice. E, F, ovicelled zooids and small, elliptical frontal avicularia. Scale bars: A = 500 µm; B = 200 µm; C, E, F = 200 µm; D = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4930717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4930717/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Figs 27 E–F</figureCitation>
owing to specimen orientation) that is typical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Osburn" authorityYear="1940" box="[274,427,440,463]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,427,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Trematooecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4930717" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4930717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4930717/files/figure.png" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" startId="44.[151,250,1939,1961]" targetBox="[187,1409,507,1906]" targetPageId="44">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1939,2016]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,292,1939,1961]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">FIGURE 27.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Canu &amp; Bassler, 1930)" baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[302,839,1939,1961]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[302,573,1939,1961]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Trematooecia hexagonalis</emphasis>
(Canu &amp; Bassler, 1930)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[853,904,1939,1961]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">A–F,</emphasis>
USNM 8513, holotype, Galápagos Islands. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1377,1435,1939,1961]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">A, B,</emphasis>
groups of zooids. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[339,364,1966,1988]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">C,</emphasis>
close-up of zooids and opercula. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[718,742,1966,1988]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">D,</emphasis>
primary orifice. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[921,972,1966,1988]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">E, F,</emphasis>
ovicelled zooids and small, elliptical frontal avicularia. Scale bars: A = 500 µm; B = 200 µm; C, E, F = 200 µm; D = 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[199,499,151,176]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[199,499,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Trematooecia hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a frontal shield with 36–51 more-or-less evenly distributed pseudopores, four solid tubercles around the secondary orifice, no suboral or interzooidal avicularia and a granular ectooecium with a median inverted slit-like membranous window. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[968,1272,223,248]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[968,1272,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Trematooecia hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tilbrook" authorityYear="2006" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="clivulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">T. clivulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ayari &amp; Taylor, 2008" authorityName="Ayari &amp; Taylor" authorityYear="2008" box="[312,827,260,285]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="ligulata">
<emphasis box="[312,563,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Trematooecia ligulata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ayari R. &amp; Taylor, P. D. &amp; Afli, A. &amp; Aissa, P." box="[575,827,260,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="261 - 267" refId="ref29611" refString="Ayari R., Taylor, P. D., Afli, A. &amp; Aissa, P. (2008) A new species of the cheilostome bryozoan Trematooecia Osburn, 1940 from the Mediterranean Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, 49, 261 - 267." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ayari &amp; Taylor, 
<quantity box="[771,827,260,285]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.10032" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" unit="in" value="2008.0">2008</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having encrusting colonies, tubercles around the secondary orifice and an ectooecium with a frontal slit, but differs in the uniformly punctured frontal shield, elliptical frontal avicularia and lack of interzooidal avicularia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Owing to the uniformly punctured frontal shield and the presence of tubercles around the secondary orifice, specimens from Atlantic coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[535,624,404,427]" name="Panama" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Panama</collectingCountry>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[666,895,404,429]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="perforata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[666,895,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Cigclisula perforata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[903,967,404,427]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; see above) and the Pacific (= 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Cigclisula osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[244,306,440,463]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, see above; see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Osburn, R. C." box="[541,691,439,464]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="271 - 611" refId="ref31697" refString="Osburn, R. C. (1952) Bryozoa of the Pacific coast of America, part 2, Cheilostomata - Ascophora. Report of the Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 14, 271 - 611." type="journal article" year="1952">Osburn 1952</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soule, J. D." box="[703,833,439,464]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 66" refId="ref32035" refString="Soule, J. D. (1961) Results of the Puritan-American Museum of Natural History expedition to western Mexico. 13. Ascophoran Cheilostomata (Bryozoa) of the Gulf of California. American Museum Novitates, 2053, 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="1961">Soule 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Soule, D. F. &amp; Soule, J. D." box="[845,1074,439,464]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref32080" refString="Soule, D. F. &amp; Soule, J. D. (1964) The Ectoprocta (Bryozoa) of Scammon's Lagoon, Baja California, Mexico. American Museum Novitates, 2199, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1964">Soule &amp; Soule 1964</bibRefCitation>
) are assigned to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1265,1428,439,464]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[1265,1428,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is distinguished by the ectooecium with a median inverted U-shape membranous area, while that in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="perforata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">C. perforata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[264,324,512,535]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[378,496,511,536]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[378,496,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">C. osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[503,563,512,535]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has irregular pseudopores.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[199,495,548,573]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[199,495,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Trematooecia hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3357128383" location="Galapagos Islands" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" specimenCount="1">
is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[778,826,548,572]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">type</typeStatus>
locality in the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:F20487E3FFE5211BF5FFF9BEFD1139E3:7F72602EFFE3211BF68FFDA0FB30395B" box="[999,1209,548,573]" name="Galapagos Islands" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Galápagos Islands</location>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Canu, F. &amp; Bassler, R. S." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref30220" refString="Canu, F. &amp; Bassler, R. S. (1930 a) The Bryozoan Fauna of the Galapagos Islands. Proceedings of United States National Museum, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, 76 (2810), 1 - 92." type="journal article" year="1930">Canu and Bassler (1930a)</bibRefCitation>
, the species encrusts shells
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
